23_23	0.094705192	Whether their forecast was a true prediction or just a lucky guess, it reinforces Dieterich's confidence in an emerging paradigm of earthquake science: the importance of crustal stress changes in triggering or inhibiting future quakes.
23_24	0.098310978	In recent years, quake specialists have developed computer models to understand how quakes change the stress on Earth's crust.
23_25	0.093966372	Some research suggests that past California quakes have been either triggered or inhibited by stress changes induced by quakes elsewhere.
23_26	0.096937211	The most dramatic example might be the great San Francisco quake of 1906, USGS geophysicist Bob Simpson said.
23_27	0.092253542	``The 1906 earthquake was such a big earthquake that it pretty much relaxed every fault in the Bay Area,'' Simpson said Wednesday.
23_28	0.087223303	As a result, for most of the 20th century California was relatively quiet, quake-wise, compared with the shaky 19th century.
